<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-554] a Node created with no value can not have children added to it.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-554</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If one creates a groovy.util.Node without specifing a value, one can not later add children to it. This is because the Node receives a default value of Collections.EMPTY_LIST and the Collections.EMPTY_LIST is immutable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following code throws an java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException exception:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;class NodeTest extends GroovyTestCase {&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    void testAdd() &lt;/p&gt;
{
	parent = new Node(null, &quot;parent&quot;);
	assert parent instanceof groovy.util.Node;
	child = new Node(parent, &quot;child&quot;);
	assert child instanceof groovy.util.Node;
    }
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One can work around this problem by always specifying a [] as the value for nodes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    void testWorkaround() &lt;/p&gt;
{
	parent = new Node(null, &quot;parent&quot;, [:], [] );
	child = new Node(parent, &quot;child&quot;, [:], [] );
	assert child instanceof groovy.util.Node;
    }</description>
